<subSubSection id="F7D86578FFAA1B1DFE2FFA5201504041" pageId="20" pageNumber="170" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="BF7D36F3FFAA1B1DFE2FFA5201504041" blockId="20.[438,1835,1151,1655]" pageId="20" pageNumber="170">
The bamboo borer occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="C7D57663FFAA1B1DFBD5FA5203764027" box="[1039,1136,1511,1553]" name="India" pageId="20" pageNumber="170">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="C7D57663FFAA1B1DFB52FA5202004027" box="[1160,1286,1511,1553]" name="Myanmar" pageId="20" pageNumber="170">Burma</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="C7D57663FFAA1B1DFAC7FA52027C4027" box="[1309,1402,1511,1553]" name="Thailand" pageId="20" pageNumber="170">Siam</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="C7D57663FFAA1B1DFA48FA5202F94027" box="[1426,1535,1511,1553]" name="China" pageId="20" pageNumber="170">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="C7D57663FFAA1B1DF9CEFA5201844027" box="[1556,1666,1511,1553]" name="Japan" pageId="20" pageNumber="170">Japan</collectingCountry>
, through the Malay Archipelago to New 
<collectingCountry id="C7D57663FFAA1B1DFBDCF9AE038E4072" box="[1030,1160,1563,1604]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="20" pageNumber="170">Guinea</collectingCountry>
. It has been known in Hawaii since 1905, doubtless introduced in bamboo furniture or other articles.
</paragraph>
